social_posts.post_text: 2022 has been a year. We’re winding down and nearing the end. Grateful for the blessings but this year has had its own share of hardships. This is one of the last photo sets of my long hair. Something I started growing out of curiosity and a burning need to know what it’s like to have. It grew on me (pun intended) and became a sentimental part of me I never expected to feel. Nevertheless, it was rewarding and a learning experience, where I became more in touch with myself as a human, and understood things about myself I never did in the past. Thanks to @imagineakira for getting these snaps of me.

Everyone has a little bit of main character energy in them.
Over the weekend I took a chainsaw to my hair.
Only real ones get the reference. ⛓️

34🎈To say the past year has been a blessing is almost an understatement. It started with me climbing out of debt and completely uncertain about my future to being hired at a job that I wake up excited and thankful for and debt free (saving a ton now). I’ve kept this quiet, but I was interviewing for engineering gigs when I was out of options at the start of 2022. I’d learned later that one of the interviewing engineering VPs made a snide remark behind my back, “How’s that photography thing working out for him?”. Suffice to say, it’s pretty pleasant to stick it to that jerk. I noticed that because of my long hair, people treated me differently, and it was fruitful to take note of that. It actually shocked me how people’s attitudes towards me changed just because of my appearance. Ever since I cut my hair, everyone has been a lot nicer for some reason. So it’s been a year of battles, proving myself, and conquering. The job is never finished but I’m very proud at all I’ve done with my 33rd year here. I’m looking forward to making the 34th even better. I feel like I’m back on the saddle and I want to take what I’ve got and continue running with it. Sorry for the long rant, but I wanted to be real with you all. Life is incredible. Thank you to all the great people who’ve kept me company along the way.
Don’t go to a photographer’s bday party if you don’t like your picture taken 📸 - Thank you for all who came out and everyone who wished me a happiest birthday! Your presence was the best presents. <3

social_posts.post_text: New profile picture 👀
can’t sleep, so here’s some photos i never posted from sometime in 2017

This picture finds its way back to the top of my feed when I feel the time is appropriate. This was the first photo I ever posted that was featured multiple times. While the number of features is arbitrary, and doing anything for the sole purpose of it being accepted on social media is something i cringe at now, it did mark an important moment for me. It made me realize that I was heading in the right direction, and I wasn’t being a fool for sharing my artwork or taking a chance at expressing myself through a visual medium. Since that photo was taken, i would end up taking several 100,000 photos more, and move into other visual mediums such as film, which i currently practice. I wager there will be many more iterations and mediums in the future that i will continue to explore and i will never stop learning. I post this to remind myself that the most important point in any journey is taking the first step. Something i feel i must do again soon. I hope that if you find yourself at this same crossroads you muster the courage to take the first step. The weight of regret is unmatched by anything else in this world.

With the year coming to an end, I reflect on all of the hard work I’ve done in my career, all of the lows and highs that got to the place I’m at right now. The struggles in the beginning made it really feel impossible and foolish to try. I look at the end of 2023 realizing odds that I never knew was possible. I’m taking all of this energy to 2024, ready to push even harder, challenge more, and reach new heights.
